#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn10.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.11:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga "
msgstr "1. With Indaka "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn10.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Cīrāsutta "
msgstr "11. With the Nun Cīrā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn10.11:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn10.11:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. VAR: cīrāya → cirāya (pts1-2, mr)

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.11:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako cīrāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ adāsi. "
msgstr "Now at that time a certain lay follower gave a robe to the nun Cīrā. "

msgctxt "sn10.11:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho cīrāya bhikkhuniyā abhippasanno yakkho rājagahe rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then a native spirit was so devoted to Cīrā that he went street to street and square to square, and on that occasion recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.460, sc2, verse-num-sc845
msgctxt "sn10.11:2.1"
msgid "“Puññaṃ vata pasavi bahuṃ, "
msgstr "“O! He has made so much merit! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.11:2.2"
msgid "Sappañño vatāyaṃ upāsako; "
msgstr "That lay-follower is so very wise. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.11:2.3"
msgid "Yo cīrāya adāsi cīvaraṃ, "
msgstr "He gave a robe to Cīrā, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: vippamuttiyā”ti → vippamuttāyāti (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn10.11:2.4"
msgid "Sabbayogehi vippamuttiyā”ti. "
msgstr "who is released from all bonds.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
